<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Okay, someone has to do this.  The way I figure it if I try I get flamed enough that we can gather all the information in one place.   <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"><P><BR>Question:  Where to put points at when starting<P>Facts:<BR>Cha has some effect on charm and mez, maybe one out of ten given the results most people get from these tests.<BR>Cha is very easy to raise at low levels, however at higher levels you'll notice that your cha items only raise cha and very few other stats.<BR>Int items tend to also raise other desired stats.<BR>At higher levels, getting over 200 int and cha is 'easy'  (defining easy and higher levels is difficult)<BR>Int increases mana pool<P><BR>Theories<BR>Cha has a huge effect on charm resists and charm duration, although given the randomness of charm this is difficult to confirm.<BR>AC, Hp, and MR are very very important stats(this really is hard to pin down, as it can depend upon the group your in, who is smart enough to use assist, if theres a cleric watching your back with root, ect.)<BR>At higher levels mana pool doesn't matter, as you'll never go oom unless theres a huge pull, at which point someone will cry for evac.<P><BR>Things we are not going to say:<BR>At all levels you should put everything into int and totally forget about cha because int rules!<BR>You should forget about cha because you are never going to charm.  I suck at charm therefor you will as well.<P><BR>Questions to ask yourself before creating enchanter:<BR>Am I going to play to a high level?  At higher levels an enchanter does nothing much besides mess and buff, and can normally end a fight with plenty of mana or dead.<BR>Will I be grouping with people who have no idea what I am there fore or will I be in outside zones the whole time where I am not needed?  At lower levels and in outside zones, enchanters don't need to/can't play crowd control due to a lack of multi pulls or stupidity in pick up groups.<BR>Will cash be a problem (do you have a high level alt or guild to twink you out or are you going to run the stein quest a lot)?  When you twink yourself out, you can change your gear depending on how you think you are going to be playing, or get both stats to high levels.<P><BR>Where to put points in for high levels:<P><I>I plan to play this character to 16 or so just to see what there doing on the other side of the fence.</I><BR>Put 25 into intellegence, then 5 points in Cha as mess wont do a lot of good or be that important in low level groups.<P><I>I am trying to figure out which class is best for me.</I><BR>Again, 25 into int and 5 into cha, as the enchanter class is hard enough as it is when you start, so you'll enjoy the mana more.<P><I>Charm rules!  I want to be able to solo well and some down time doesnt bother me.</I><BR>25 points in Cha if you like it that much, then 5 points in something else.  What is the something else?  Well just remember, charm doesnt use a huge amount of mana and lasts awhile, but when charm breaks its going for your throat.  Adding to agility or something may help you get the re-charm off, or the stun root nuke.<P><I>God I love nuke spells!  they do so much damage.</I><BR>Go make a wizard with 25 in int    <IMG SRC="tongue.gif" border="0"> <P><I>I have a guild/higher level player to twink me out.</I><BR>Well, twinking doesn't work as well at higher levels, so it doesn't matter what you put it in till higher levels.  Depends on what equipment you have<P><I>I have played all other classes to level 45+ and I feel like a real challenge that will have huge bonuses in the end.  I play 6 hours a day on average and I don't mind a bit of hard work.</I><BR>Put all your points in something other than int or cha.  You'll get them both at 200+ easily enough at level 60, and those 25 and 5 points in stamina or something will be really nice at higher levels.<BR>Or put it all in cha as int items have nice plusses to stamina and such built in<P>Okay, flame away.  I don't have a high level enchanter, this is supposed to be flamed.  hopefully enough information will be posted that a new character can look at it and figure something out.
</FONT>
