<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Not a flame just some things I see differently after 52 lvls.<P>Yes CHA does have an effect and the affect is positively influenced by CHA about 1 out of 25 times or so.  <P>The part about cha having a huge affect on charm is a little off.  According to a recent post someone tried 2 runs of 25 attempts per charm and the one with ~150 lower cha had greater average length.  This was probably has to do with the random number generator but we can see that the effect cant be that high because if it was the lower cha would have HAD TO have less average length.  Also one of the low cha tests had the greatest total length as well.<P>Also at high levels mana pool does matter and even with theft and ~200 INT and ~+150 mana at lvl 52 I still get pretty low sometimes and a lot of deaths are because of OOM enchanters/clerics.<P>I do agree about the MR thing, although its because I dont want other players root/mezzing me and you dont want to hit yourself with youre AE mez.  Same end result MR is good.  I have ~160.<P>I dont agree with the "dont say this section" IMHO it would be better to say that It wont hurt you much to put all into INT and some into str/sta/agi because the cha wont affect you that much and its the easiest to raise if later on cha starts to matter.<BR>The cha part ive already told my spiel on, If you want better success with mez/charm fight lower blues and dont worry about youre CHA.<P>I am "high" level and I do a lot more than mez and buff, and do run OOM a lot especially when I dont want to.<P>If you are charming and for some reason want 200 cha and put 25 into this at the character creation then you will have to find some major $$ int items to go in the wrist and necklace jewlery slots which make up 25 cha by themselves.  I dont know any combination of (2) wrist/finger items and a necklace that will make 25 INT, that you can get at a level when you would want to charm solo.<P>Nuke spells.  I use these a lot both in PVP and PVE.  After all I do have theft and the other casters dont for the most part (wizards have a spell that doesnt make mobs lose mana and only works every 5th time (or more) theft does).  This gives me a lot of mana, so much that I can almost out damage wizards over the course of a night of exp.  All that while keeping everything mez/slow/buffed.<P>Also add another (2) facts:<BR>INT will give you the mana you need to use your low power DD's to solo until you can get breeze and people will want to group with you.<BR>INT will give you more maximum mana which, when it comes down to train stopping, means all the difference(dont count on clarify here).<P>Tsunamii Starshine<BR>52 Enchantress Rallos Zek<P>--------------------<P>Tsunamii Starshine
</FONT>
